[size=6][b]The Longest Year[/b][/size]
[size=4][i]Restore the Community Center within a single year — or the Junimos rewind the seasons and you begin again, a little stronger.[/i][/size]

[color=yellow][b]BETA (0.9.6).[/b] Feature-complete and stable in testing. What it needs now is your feedback on difficulty, pricing, and pacing — see the bottom of this page.[/color]

[line]

[size=5][b]What's New in 0.9.6[/b][/size]
Changes since the first beta (0.9.2):
[list]
[*][b]The Community Center bulletin board works now.[/b] Walking up to the Mixed room's bulletin board did nothing before — it now opens like the other five rooms, so you can donate to it from day one.
[*][b]Other saves are left completely alone.[/b] Loading a normal (non-TLY) save with the mod installed now does nothing at all — no effects, no HUD, no year-rewind. Starting a new game is the only way to begin a run, and existing runs carry over automatically.
[*][b]Update notifications.[/b] SMAPI now tells you in its console when a new version is available.
[/list]
Earlier betas (0.9.0–0.9.2) shipped the full loop, the porch + Junimo intro, the win screen, and the new-loop picker fix. Full history in [url=https://github.com/sonofskywalker3/TheLongestYear/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md]CHANGELOG.md[/url].

[line]

[size=5][b]What it is[/b][/size]
The Longest Year turns Stardew's first year into a roguelite loop. Each season, you must give back enough of the land's bounty to the old Community Center hall. Fall short by a season's end and the Junimos turn time back to Spring 1 — the world resets, but the strength you've earned, and the power your offerings have banked, can carry forward. Restore the whole Center inside one year to break the loop for good.

[size=5][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Seasonal time-loop.[/b] Each season has a donation minimum. Miss it and the year unwinds to Spring 1.
[*][b]Junimo Points.[/b] Donations earn JP — scaled by rarity and by how late in the year you give. JP banks across loops.
[*][b]The Junimo Shrine.[/b] Spend JP on upgrades that let you hold on to some of what you gained: skill levels, tool tiers, recipes, buildings, a kept pet, and more.
[*][b]Weekly themes.[/b] Each week, pick a theme that grants a bonus and a paired liability. Plan around it.
[*][b]Carryover surfaces.[/b] A Bundle Log book that tracks each season's goals, a Cookbook and Craftbook to bank recipes, and a Junimo Stash chest that survives resets.
[*][b]A real intro.[/b] Lewis greets you on the porch; a Junimo explains the loop. Then the run begins.
[*][b]Break the loop.[/b] Finish the Center in a year to win — then keep playing or start fresh.
[/list]

[size=5][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Stardew Valley 1.6+ (PC)
[*]SMAPI 4.0.0+
[*]A [b]new save[/b] on the [b]Standard farm[/b]
[/list]

[size=5][b]Install[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Install SMAPI 4.0.0 or newer.
[*]Unzip into your [font=Courier New]Stardew Valley/Mods[/font] folder.
[*]Launch through SMAPI and [b]start a new game on the Standard farm[/b]. Farm-type and intro options are handled for you.
[/list]

[size=5][b]Limitations (beta)[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]PC only — no Android port yet.
[*]Standard farm only.
[*]A run can only be started from a new game (other saves load normally and are left untouched).
[*]Intro cutscene and dialogue are a first pass.
[*]Multiplayer untested.
[/list]

[size=5][b]Tuning[/b][/size]
Everything difficulty-related lives in [font=Courier New]config.json[/font] — JP values, per-season multipliers, completion bonuses, starting gold, and per-bundle quotas. Tweak freely and tell me what felt right.

[line]

[size=5][b]Feedback wanted[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Difficulty[/b] — are the seasonal minimums fair? Which wall hit hardest?
[*][b]Pricing[/b] — do JP earnings and shrine costs feel balanced? What did you save for first?
[*][b]Pacing[/b] — how many loops before it "clicked"? Did carryover make later loops feel stronger?
[*][b]Bugs[/b] — please attach your [font=Courier New]SMAPI-latest.txt[/font] (from [font=Courier New]Stardew Valley/ErrorLogs/[/font]).
[/list]

[line]

[size=5][b]Art wanted[/b][/size]
The mod leans on vanilla sprites throughout. If anyone would enjoy making some custom book/sprite artwork (the Cookbook and Craftbook especially), I'd genuinely love to accept it and credit you. Drop a note in the comments.

[i]Banner art by [b]cwybabiesucks[/b] — thank you![/i]

